			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Who is Social Envi?</strong><br />
Social Envi is a social media marketing agency, founded in 2010. Our company builds social environments designed to engage brands with their customers and prospects. Based in Los Angeles, CA, we&rsquo;re a fun-loving bunch who thinks that what we do for work is fun.</p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re strategists, graphic designers, bloggers, community managers, copywriters, multi-media producers and futurists. Granted, it&rsquo;s not brain surgery, but as seasoned pros, we&rsquo;re passionate, even a little obsessed, about being the best at what we do. (Beats a &ldquo;real&rdquo; job, anyway.)</p>
<p>
<strong>Your Mission (Should you choose to accept it)</strong><br />
Stick like glue between the client and our creative teams to make sure everything stays on track. Work well with clients and keep them happy, but also play well with others as part of a larger internal team.</p>
<ul>
<li>
The client will have you on speed dial, and expect you to be able to provide counsel, programming ideas, or solutions to whatever challenges may arise.</li>
<li>
Work with Sales to help create proposals, budgets and project outlines.</li>
<li>
Write and review strategic reports and creative plans for clients.</li>
<li>
Lead weekly client meetings to discuss performance, schedules, creative direction, and deadlines, after a little light schmoozing.</li>
<li>
Draft reports, strategies, plans, research audits and submit them to clients for approval.</li>
<li>
Seek new ways to grow the client&rsquo;s business (and ours).</li>
<li>
Coordinate and present weekly, monthly and quarterly project reports to the client.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Enough about us, let&rsquo;s talk about you:</strong><br />
You&rsquo;re a leader and a socializer who&rsquo;s passionate about social media. You make connections easily and enjoy meeting new people. You know how to sell without being too &ldquo;salesy&rdquo;.</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Hunter-gatherer personality (farmers need not apply) with 1-3 years sales experience.</li>
<li>
Creative, intelligent, tech-savvy, hard-working, and fun-loving.</li>
<li>
You can lead, plan, organize, and manage projects.</li>
<li>
You write and speak good (and can recognize and avoid poor grammar like that).</li>
<li>
Bachelor&#39;s Degree (Marketing, Business, Strategy, Psychology, Engineering, or related).</li>
<li>
Understand the marketing roles of digital and social media.</li>
<li>
Understand owned and earned online media.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Extra Credit:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Serious blogger.</li>
<li>
Steve Jobsian presentation skills.</li>
<li>
Budgeting ability.</li>
<li>
Client Services experience.</li>
<li>
CPG and/or food industry knowledge.</li>
<li>
Large agency background.</li>
<li>
&hearts; bacon.</li>
</ul>
