<strong>Who is Social Envi?</strong><br />
Social Envi is a social media marketing organization, founded in 2010. Our company builds social environments designed to engage brands with their customers and prospects. Based in Los Angeles, CA, we&rsquo;re a fun-loving bunch who thinks that what we do for work is fun.</p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re strategists, graphic designers, bloggers, community managers, copywriters, multi-media producers and futurists. Granted, it&rsquo;s not brain surgery, but as seasoned pros, we&rsquo;re passionate, even a little obsessed, about being the best at what we do. (Beats a &ldquo;real&rdquo; job, anyway.)</p>
<p>
<strong>Your mission (should you choose to accept it)</strong><br />
As an Associate Community Manager, you&rsquo;re like an online matchmaker. You introduce customers to our clients via social networks, then act like a chaperone, keeping an eye on things and making new introductions. No actual dating involved.</p>
<p>
Still not juicy enough? Here&rsquo;s some more. As Associate Community Manager, you&rsquo;ll be expected to:</p>
<p>
<u>Create Conversation Calendars:</u> Give &lsquo;em something to talk about. Help write blog posts and marketing messages to post and distribute to the community. Calendars are typically produced weekly or monthly.</p>
<p>
<u>Develop Incentives/Promotions:</u> Everybody likes swag. Here, you get give it away. Social promotions can be coupon codes, free merch, surveys, sweepstakes, product trial/reviews, free samples. You&rsquo;ll be in charge of it all.</p>
<p>
<u>Outreach to Influencers/Bloggers:</u> Figure out who the movers and shakers are. See who can serve as a paid or unpaid influencer from among a brand&rsquo;s following. Influencer-Bloggers may get exclusive content, client access, swag, or other compensation for their participation and promotion.</p>
<p>
<u>Develop Reports:</u> Keep tabs on progress. Produce regular reports on your performance vs. client benchmarks. Use Facebook Insights, Radian6 and other key social reporting tools. Our Research &amp; Analytics team will support you as needed.</p>
<ul>
<li>
Summarize insights and conversations to create actionable, client-facing reports that lead to optimization.</li>
<li>
Create and update daily, weekly and monthly reports.</li>
<li>
Analyze campaigns and translate anecdotal or qualitative data into recommendations and plans for revising the social media campaigns.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<u>Moderate and Respond:</u> Be a gracious host/hostess. Review user-generated comments and posts in a timely manner. Reply to comments (as appropriate) to foster a positive community. Follow each brand&rsquo;s Social Media Guidelines.</p>
<p>
Remember, our account team has your back. We&rsquo;ll provide both mentorship and partnership.</p>
<p>
<strong>Let&rsquo;s talk about you:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
You&rsquo;ve been around the block: 2+ years of experience in social media, community management, digital, or related field</li>
<li>
Bachelor degree (preferably in digital media, marketing, communications or related field)</li>
<li>
Speak, write, and present like a pro</li>
<li>
You can translate jargon</li>
<li>
Spin multiple plates while to meeting deadlines</li>
<li>
PowerPoint ninja, Mac fluent</li>
<li>
Right-brain/left-brain ambidextrous</li>
<li>
Social on YouTube, StumbleUpon, Delicious, Digg, Reddit, Flickr, Forums, Twitter, Wikis, blogs, etc.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Bonus Points</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Blogger with Klout</li>
<li>
Agency experience</li>
<li>
HTML, CSS and Photoshop don&rsquo;t scare you</li>
<li>
The name Tom Anderson means something</li>
<li>
Photography skills beyond Instagram</li>
<li>
Handy with a Digital SLR camera</li>
<li>
You started a meme</li>
</ul>
